{"lemma":"نَعْلَيْ","slug":"نَعْلَيْ","root":"ن.ع.ل","root_slug":"ن-ع-ل","root_link":"/words/roots/ن-ع-ل","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"نَعْلَيْ","root":"نعل","pos":"N","occurrence_count":1},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":12,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":7},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["","n44040"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%86%D9%8E%D8%B9%D9%92%D9%84%D9%8E%D9%8A%D9%92"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to sole, to shoe"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be shoed"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to sole, to shoe"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of نَعَلَ (naʕala) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"any covering for human or animal feet, a shoe (such as human footwear or a horseshoe)","tags":["dated"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"a light shoe for human feet (such as a slipper)","tags":["Arabic","Modern","Standard"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of نَعِلَ (naʕila) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"* Compare for the “shoe” noun Classical Syriac ܢܥܠܐ (naʿlā), Hebrew נַעַל (náʿal)\n* Perhaps related to Ge'ez ንዑልት (nəʿult), ኑዑልት (nuʿult, “widow married by levirate marriage”) because, according to Dillmann, the ceremony of the levirate marriage seems to involve the bridegroom throwing a shoe in the biblical passages where it is found – but this Ethiopic word is perhaps from Cushitic; Cushitic was unknown in Dillmann’s time, which forced Semitic explanations of Ethiopic.\n* Likely related to Akkadian 𒈿 (nâlu, niālu, “to lie down”) and its derivations related to “spreading”\n* In the view of this general “spreading” meaning in Akkadian, likely related to Ugaritic 𐎐𐎓𐎍 (nʿl) which is variously glossed: “palanquin”, “sandal”, “robe”\n* ➜ Apparently the later Semitic languages have specialised a “spreading” meaning to a “shoeing” meaning\n\nSee the etymology of the corresponding lemma form."},"ipa":["/na.ʕa.la/","/na.ʕi.la/","/naʕ.ʕa.la/","/naʕl/","/na.ʕal/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n44040","headword_ar":"نَعْلٌ","root":"nEl","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A sandal: a sole:"},{"kind":"text","text":"] the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thing by which the foot is preserved,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"protected, from the ground;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K;) syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hi*aA='N","text_ar":"حِذَا=ءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": and also applied to"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taAsuwmap","text_ar":"تَاسُومَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"shoe"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Msb.)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"What is now called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taAsuwmap","text_ar":"تَاسُومَة"},{"kind":"text","text":". (IAth, TA.) It often signifies only"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a sole:"},{"kind":"text","text":"so in the S, K, Msb, &c., in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xSf","text_ar":"خصف"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c. ―         -b2-  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"leathern shoe,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sandal,"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a camel;"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"which is attached by thongs,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"straps, called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saraAy^iH","text_ar":"سَرَايِح"},{"kind":"text","text":"(pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sariyHapN","text_ar":"سَرِيحَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xadamap","text_ar":"خَدَمَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"plaited thong which surrounds the pastern:"},{"kind":"text","text":"see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sariyHapN","text_ar":"سَرِيحَ